Roles & Responsibilities
Job Summary
We are seeking for a self-motivated Data Analyst with data management and testing experience within the banking and financial industry.
Mandatory Skill-set
Degree in Business Computing, Computer Science, or equivalent;
3-5 years of experience in data/business analysis and testing in banking industry;
Proficient in SQL and Microsoft Office;
Experience in liaising with IT and users;
Maintain strong analytical, problem-solving, and communicating skills;
Develop and perform SIT/UAT test cases for data quality rules;
Self-motivated, resourceful, and possess exquisite time management skills.
Desired Skill-set
Knowledge in Data Warehousing, BI tools, Big Data platforms;
Familiar with Metadata tools.
Responsibilities
Gathering and documenting business requirements & functional specifications on data related initiatives;
Perform data investigation and data analysis to support Bank wide users' queries on EDAG;
Perform data profiling and gap analysis, source to target mappings, data issue capturing, resolution and escalation;
Provide end-to-end project delivery support, including requirements walkthrough, user acceptance testing;
Execute data analysis and data investigation;
Conduct end-to-end User Acceptance Test (UAT) process;
Manage business glossary and dashboards for review and analytical purposes;
Assist the entire project implementations.
Should you be interested in this career opportunity, please send in your updated resume to apply@sciente.com at the earliest.
When you apply, you voluntarily consent to the disclosure, collection and use of your personal data for employment/recruitment and related purposes in accordance with the SCIENTE Group Privacy Policy, a copy of which is published at SCIENTE’s website (https://www.sciente.com/privacy-policy).
Confidentiality is assured, and only shortlisted candidates will be notified for interviews.
EA Licence No. 07C5639

Roles & Responsibilities
Job Duties:
The activities required to be performed shall include the following:
Provide application support and maintenance for Dashboard on Microsoft Power BI including designing of new dashboards;
Provide support and maintenance for data lake/data warehouse;
Maintain and implement data ingestion pipeline;
Define and implement data acquisition and integration logic;
Participate/Lead in end-to-end Software Development Lifecycle (SDLC) activities for change requests and new projects, including requirement gathering, design, development, testing and deployment;
Interpret and analyze data to answer key problems defined by stakeholders;
Creation and maintenance of documentations, provide audit support and ensure system compliance.

Job Requirements:
The qualification and work experience required are as follows:
Recognised qualification in Computer Science or a relevant discipline;
Minimum 2 years of hands-on experience in data ETL using Python, SQL, etc.;
Experience with data visualizations software such as Microsoft Power BI, Tableau, etc.;
Proficient in systems analysis, data design, data lake management and service management;
Strong analytical, problem solving and programming skills;
Self-driven, able to multi-task and work independently, a good team player and possesses good analytical, interpersonal and written/verbal communication skills;
Preferably with experience on user support, analytic platform and knowledge on cloud technologies;
Experience with Amazon Web Services data analytics tools, Microstrategy Analytics, MicroStrategy HyperIntelligence or Informatica PowerCenter will be an added advantage;
Knowledge of tools and techniques in machine learning, statistical modelling & analytics will be an added advantage;
Interested candidates may apply with detailed CV to patrina@eps.com.sg stating your expected salary and availability.

Roles & Responsibilities
Job Summary

A great opportunity as a Data Engineer to work in cloud based data engineering and data management within the financial sector.

Mandatory Skill-set
Bachelor's Degree in Computer Science or equivalent;
Minimum 3 years of experience in data engineering or software engineering;
Possess a solid foundation in Computer Science concepts such as Cloud Computing Architecture, Distributed Computing, High-Velocity Data Processing, and Lambda Architecture;
Proficient in Data modeling and managing Distributed Computing Platforms for efficient Data Processing;
Strong hands-on experience on SQL and Pyspark;
Thorough understanding of Kubernetes clusters and their scalability capabilities;
Demonstrated implementation of manual or automated tools for Data Quality, Catalog, and Lineage;
Excellent interpersonal and presentation skills to effectively communicate and advocate for Best Practices across the organization, catering to both technical and non-technical stakeholders.
Desired Skill-set
Certifications in AWS.
Responsibilities
Extensive expertise in constructing Data Pipelines utilizing Spark on AWS EMR or Glue;
Orchestrating Batch Pipelines through Apache Airflow;
Deploying jobs on AWS EKS (Kubernetes);
Implementing a Code Repository Pipeline for automating Continuous Integration and Continuous Deployment (CI/CD);
Enhancing Cost and Performance Benefits by structuring tables with Partitioning and Clustering;
Providing guidance to Data Analysts and Data Scientists to optimize queries and workloads;
Enabling secure Data Sharing with scalable On-Demand Encryption/Decryption capabilities;
Executing Containerized ETL workflows at a large scale.

